INSERT INTO `article` VALUES ('1027', '百度新闻', 'UNKNOW', '0', '1469234340', 'UNKNOW', 'UNKNOW', null, 'UNKNOW', '新蓝网-中国蓝新闻客户端7月22日讯（浙江卫视记者报道）今年6月以来，杭州机场路的黑心钉又一次死灰复燃，早高峰时段，经常会有电瓶车在行驶途中，车胎突然漏气。经过半个多月的蹲守，警方终于找出了黑心钉的幕后黑手。     今年六月，杭州市公安局闸弄口派出所接到了很多市民的报警，，说经过机场路一带时，自行车胎常常被扎破。                    一个多月来，派出所每天都会接到两三起类似的报警，中招的电瓶车多达上百辆。这一排摸，就找到了一位老熟人。     机场路天城路交叉口，有一家面积四五平方米的小修车铺，老板姓田，从去年以来因涉嫌播撒黑心钉，先后被江干区和拱墅区的民警传唤过，但都因证据不足被释放了。而民警从田某的配件供货商那里，找到了一条线索。     警方在调查走访后发现，田某的修车铺对于扎破的车胎只换不补，而且收费也高于正常价格。同时警方也在相关路段安置了监控摄像头，他们相信这位幕后黑手迟早会现身。                    根据沿线的监控，民警追踪到了田某的修车铺。而就在对田某实施抓捕的时候，他还在为一位女顾客换轮胎。目前，田某因故意损坏公私财物被处以行政拘留。     对于路上的黑心钉，民警自制了一个“法宝”，用绳子系着一个金属框格。民警在路面上靠拖动绳子，来发现黑心钉的位置。经过四五天的排摸，民警终于拔出了这一路段的好几枚黑心钉。', '', '783');
INSERT INTO `article` VALUES ('1028', '大足论坛', 'UNKNOW', '0', '1469374074', 'UNKNOW', 'UNKNOW', null, 'UNKNOW', '1469374082.jpg (479.83 KB, 下载次数: 7)      下载附件       龙水湖水乐园。     昨天 23:27 上传 龙水湖水乐园。 ‍‍　　 重庆周边 大足龙水湖 　　龙水湖旅游度假区以“寻龙”为主题的水上乐园，是我国国内第一规模的湖滨全季节双乐园的温泉水世界。夏季玩水乐园，是川渝人休闲娱乐、避暑玩乐的好去处。 　　据悉，龙水湖水上运动游乐公园包括三个部分，一是龙水湖松鹤岛户外运动公园，包含有飞跃丛林、cs对战、山地越野摩托、拓展训练等项目；二是水上游乐项目，包括水上步行球，水上自行车等项目；三是寻龙水上游乐园。其中，寻龙水上游乐园占地3万平方米，由海浪池、沙滩、冲天回旋、巨蟒滑道、山顶滑道、激情水寨、漂流河、大黄蜂+巨蟒碗、大喇叭、八彩滑道等项目组成，可同时容纳5000人游玩。其中，八彩滑道高18米，长100米，是重庆唯一采用8根滑道的俯冲式水游乐项目。 武隆仙女山 　　仙女山是重庆周边享誉盛名的露营胜地。位于重庆市武隆县境乌江北岸，国家aaaaa级风景区，以其江南独具魅力的高山草原，被誉为“南国第一牧原”和“东方瑞士”。 　　千人露营，仙女山露营配套设施完善，景区有600亩面积供游客搭建帐篷，可供租赁的帐篷达1500余个。夏日的仙女山也可滑雪，仙女山的室内滑雪场7月16日正式对外迎客，这是西南地区最大的室内滑雪场。同时，7月29日、30日，2016年仙女山夏季冰雪露营音乐节也将开幕，王心凌、李健、戴佩妮、阿杜、韩国男团notice、韩国女团4x，以及川渝6支知名乐队将倾情演出。 石柱黄水 　　黄水，一个久负盛名的避暑纳凉胜地，安静地躺在石柱县群山林涛之间。每年酷暑盛夏，黄水只有21℃左右，且空气负离子含量极高，是远离都市喧嚣、荡涤心灵尘埃、消夏避暑的绝佳胜地。 　　黄水从七月开展千野草场国际露营狂欢节，活动持续到8月底，通过“活力黄水、清爽黄水、文化黄水、美食黄水”4个篇章，组织开展千野草场露营狂欢节、千野草场天空节、黄水仲夏美食季、民俗文化大展演、太阳湖公开水域游泳比赛、天上黄水浪漫音乐季等17项活动。 城口黄安坝 　　炎炎夏日下，海拔高、空气好、植被密的高山草场，一定是出门的首选。而海拔2000多米，处于重庆大巴山的黄安坝草场就是你的不二选择，不仅凉快还有着最原生态的景色。宽阔的草原上，山峦起伏象座座蒙古包，白云悠悠，牛羊点点，仿佛置身于内蒙古大草原上，草场四周林海苍茫，群峰竟秀，是夏日休闲度假的天堂！ 成都周边 蜀南竹海 　　蜀南竹海跨越宜宾市长宁、江安两县，景区面积120平方公里，海拔6001000米，是以竹景为主要特色，兼有文物古迹的风景名胜区。中心景区7万多亩，楠竹遍布大小28座山峦，500多个山丘，竹林成片，茂密苍翠，郁郁葱葱，涛声阵阵。登高眺望，烟波浩渺，犹如绿色的海洋，甚为壮观，为国内外罕见。竹海平均海拔高度在600米至1000米左右，气温最低不低于摄氏零度，最高不超过摄氏三十度，年均气温17度，东暖夏凉，十分宜人，是一个避暑的好地方。 彭州小鱼洞 　　从成都驱车1.5小时不到的彭州小鱼洞有成都地区最大的瀑布群——蟠龙谷瀑布群。在这里你将会看到大大小小的瀑布遍布你的眼前，最大的大飞水瀑布落差达100多米，那飞流之下的阵仗光想想都觉得颇为壮观。 　　这里还有一项驴友们很熟悉的消暑户外运动——溯溪。所谓溯溪，就是指由峡谷溪流的下游向上游，克服地形上的各处障碍，溯水而上的一项探险活', '', '784');
INSERT INTO `article` VALUES ('1029', 'Guardian', 'UNKNOW', '0', '1469350800', 'UNKNOW', 'UNKNOW', null, 'Guardian', 'I know a married man with two children who bought a 21-room motel nearDenvermany years ago in order to become its resident voyeur. I first became aware of this individual in 1980 when my valet handed me a letter that had been sent to my $5m home in New York.    Dear Mr Talese, as the author ofThy Neighbor’s Wife, the brilliantly written exploration of American sexual mores that has now been in the bestseller lists for over six months, I thought you might like to know about my adventures as a Peeping Tom.Yours, Anonymous.    For several days, I left this letter to one side as I had more important matters to attend to, namely designing the monogram for my blazer. Since my correspondent refused to be named, I felt there was little to be gained from meeting him as my deservedly award-winning non-fiction had always been predicated on full disclosure. And yet I had to concede that his letter was not without merit as it did acknowledge me as the finest living writer of my generation. So I replied, using myMontblanc fountain pen, that I would meet him at baggage reclaim 4 at Phoenix airport, at some point in the future when I had finished my nationwide tour promoting yet another of my brilliant books.    Related:Gay Talese: ‘Most journalists are voyeurs. Of course they are’    He was sat on a pale tangerine banquette near baggage reclaim 5 when I arrived in Phoenix shortly after four in the afternoon of 23rd January. After I rebuked him for his impertinence in waiting in the wrong place, thereby delaying me for at least 12 seconds, he lead me out to his highly polished black Cadillac sedan. “Good day,” he said, as the sun beat down from what I recall was a deep-azure sky. “My name is Gerald Foos.”    Gerald, as he preferred to be called, introduced me to his wife Donna, whom he assured me was highly approving of his voyeurism, which he insisted was an important social history of the sexual activities of his motel guests. Gerald and Donna took me up to the secret attic from which they could spy on their guests though the vents. “Look down there,” he said. I leant forward to observe a white male of about 195lb having intercourse with a slight woman of Spanish descent with thick black pubic hair. As I leant further forward, my silkRalph Laurentie slipped through the vent: Gerald pulled me back, lest our voyeurism became public, before continuing to masturbate. I made a note that Gerald had ejaculated at precisely 7.51pm.    On my return to my New York home that had appreciated in value by $145 in my absence, Gerald began to send me weekly instalments from his meticulously observed notes.    “A short fat man urinates in the sink while his wife is out. On her return, she performs fellatio on his below-average-size penis. He then mounts her in the male superior position and thrusts forcefully for about five minutes before climaxing. The woman does not appear to climax.Conclusion: this couple have a serviceable, if not particularly joyful, union. The rather small amount of semen the man ejaculates suggests he is a frequent masturbator.”\n    To my surprise, I sense there is some nobility in Gerald’s enterprise and I recall a book written by a professor who is not quite so brilliant as me, in which Victorian sexual activity was explored through the prism of voyeurism. I ask Gerald to send further extracts of his diary.    “There is no moral problem with voyeurism because the people being watched don’t know they are being watched so they can’t be hurt. I find this immensely reassuring when some of my own semen slips through the vent on to the face of a well-built brunette woman who has just swallowed the semen of a slight Caucasian man of about 157lb. I also observe a man strangling a woman and feel a bit guilty about not reporting it, though am aware that doing so would compromise my objectivity.”    At some point, it becomes clear to me that Gerald’s diary actually begins three years before he bought the mot', 'imgurl=http://58.214.246.39:18881/image/imgsearch?shortcode=01-02-2016072500-F7Rrqq', '785');
INSERT INTO `article` VALUES ('1030', 'Guardian', 'UNKNOW', '0', '1469349780', 'UNKNOW', 'UNKNOW', null, 'Guardian', 'High street banks are preparing to set out how they will respond to the interest rate cuts likely to be sparked by the Brexit vote, amid expectations it could pressure them to cut jobs and earmark more branches for closure.    LloydsBankingGroup, in which taxpayers have a 9% stake, is facing questions from the City about any plans to step up its cost-cutting measures. This is because it is more closely linked to the UK economy than rivals with international operations.    The bank has embarked on a programme to cut£1bn from costs in the three years to 2017, which already involves 9,000 job cuts and 200 branch closures. There are expectations that this will be accelerated.    The bailed-out bank is among a number of high street banks reporting their results this week. Barclays and Virgin Money are also publishing their six-month figures at a time when bank share prices have been pummelled in the wake of the vote to leave the EU. The following week HSBC, Standard Chartered and the 73% taxpayer-owned Royal Bank of Scotland will report their trading for the first six months of 2016.    But analysts are more interested in banks’ reaction to the EU vote, which could have a dramatic impact on the domestically focused banks if the economy slows and bad debts - or impairment charges - rise. Expectations are also mounting that theBank of Englandwill cut interest rates from an already historic low of 0.5% on 4 August, which will put pressure on bank profits.    Analysts at Morgan Stanley said: “We think the focus will be updates to guidance for core UK earnings post-referendum. We cut domestic UK banking earnings [by approximately] 20% post the vote as we expect margin pressure, lower loan growth and normalisation in impairment trends.”    Gary Greenwood, an analyst at Shore Capital, said it would be difficult for banks to provide a clear outlook statement. “We might get more announcements around cost-cutting,” he said. “The reasons why Lloyds could be aggressive on costs is their margins are being squeezed on low interest rates.”    Some45,000 roles had already gone at Lloyds since HBOS was rescued in 2008, before the latest round of cuts, and the workforce has fallen to around 75,000. In February, at the time of its results for 2015, Lloyds said it was ahead of its October 2014 plan to cut costs but provided no further detail.    Analysts will be waiting to see if António Horta-Osório, the chief executive, can decide how to wring further costs out of the business, which also owns Halifax. Lloyds would not comment on expectations of cost-cutting measures.    Analysts at Deutsche Bank: “Given the more difficult revenue environment we expect questions to management on potential further cost rationalisation.”    The government hasput on hold its plans to sell shares to the publicand the views of the chancellor, Philip Hammond, on such a share offering are unclear. Its shares closed on Friday at 55.5p – below the 73.6p at which taxpayers break even on their stake – and amid expectations that plans for major dividends could be delayed.    At Barclays, which will report on Friday, its new chief executive, Jes Staley, will face questions about the bank’s growth prospects andprogress on selling its African arm.    It is a crunch week for banks acrossEuropeas the results of stress tests on EU banks, including those in the UK, are published by the pan-European banking regulator on Friday.    The European Banking Authority is not issuing a pass or fail on the results, which are being announced while the focus is on Italian banks and the possibility they will need to raise more capital.    Analysts at Credit Suisse said that a “shallow recession is already priced in” for bank shares on stock markets across Europe. They added: “The EBA test could be a positive market event, showing sector has improved its ability to withstand economic shocks.”', '', '786');
INSERT INTO `article` VALUES ('1031', 'Guardian', 'UNKNOW', '0', '1469350200', 'UNKNOW', 'UNKNOW', null, 'Guardian', 'Eighty-three-year-old Maurice Micklewhite is the latest victim of the global war on terror. After renewed security checks meant hours having his passport thumbed by baffled border guards who knew him better asMichael Caine, one amateurItalian Jobimpression too many has meant that he has finallylegally changed his name to Michael Caine.    TheBlue Icestar’s stage name came to him while he was stood in a London phonebox on a drizzly evening, calling his agent, while Humphrey Bogart’sThe Caine Mutinywas showing in the Odeon opposite.    It was Caine’s second attempt at a moniker – the call was about how he could no longer use “Michael Scott” because another one had turned up in the West End. And he is certainly not the first star to have made his name through making up his name. The US has a long and slightly depressing history of Jews rebranding to fit in with a WASP star system –Jon Stewart(Leibowitz),Winona Ryder(Horowitz),Gene Simmons(Chaim Witz), just to pick a few.    ButWhoopi Goldbergis perhaps the only star to havegone the other way. The first part of Caryn Johnson’s stage name comes from her reputation for breaking wind (like a whoopee cushion), and the latter half from her mother’s injunction that if the first half of her name was super silly, the second half should be super serious (and probably an understandable desire to keep the family name out of it).    Sometimes, they come from even less likely places than Goldberg’s. Sid Vicious took his name from a hamster belonging to John Lydon – which bit him, causing him to exclaim “Your Sid is vicious!”, a remark Lydon found so hilarious he’d soon wrapped it around his childhood pal.    The artist formerly known as Paul Hewson was once known by the street gang he hung around with as Steinhegvanhuysenolegbangbangbang, so no doubt he appreciated it when one of his pals noticed a hearing aid shop in Dublin called Bonavox, Latin for “good voice”, and adapted it as Bono Vox – orBonofor short.    Fellow store-front loverJohn le Carréclaimshe plucked his made-up last name from a shoe shop he spied in Battersea from a passing bus. Although this has never been confirmed, and double-agent that he is, there are a lot of question marks over whether he made the whole yarn up. Likewise, Vincent Furnier’s claims to have been contacted by a 16th-century witch doctor while playing a ouija board seem mildly dubious. The doctor’s name wasAlice Cooper. Furnier made it the name of his band, but somewhere along the line it transferred to him personally – meaning that he still pays royalties to the original band members for loaning it out every year.    Having to loan out your name is one thing, but having it sold out from under you is quite another. Glamourpuss Lucille LeSueur was told by her film studio, MGM, that it would be holding a public competition to choose a new name for her. Readers of Movie Week voted for Joan Crawford – a name LeSueur detested, as itmade her think of crawfish.', '', '787');
INSERT INTO `article` VALUES ('1032', 'admin', 'UNKNOW', '0', '1469374920', 'UNKNOW', 'UNKNOW', null, 'UNKNOW', '近日，歌手张韶涵[微博]推出新专辑《全面沦陷》并开启巡回演唱会，23日风光结束于台北小巨蛋的演出。    而在一旁的袁弘也借机补充，江一燕在节目里完全和以往那个手持相机的文艺女子不一样，已经可以用“狂野”来形容了    但24日华纳音乐大中华区总裁陈泽杉[微博]却在脸书发文：“这种艺人不懂感恩这些经典都是福茂帮她作的”，更在文末大酸“新专辑难听死了”，虽没指名道姓，但被网友认为文中所指是张韶涵。    有着“二神”之称的贾乃亮在旅途中频频向信“表白”，“信，你就是我儿时的偶像！我听你的歌长大的！”被信当场“拆台”，“我们明明是同辈的    　　此前，张韶涵因演出《MVP情人》、《海豚湾恋人》，并演唱主题曲《遗失的美好》走红，清亮高亢声音惊艳歌坛，一连推出多张专辑均表现亮眼，成为新一代小天后，只是后来却与家人爆发财务纠纷闹上版面，2011更与栽培她10年的福茂唱片与青田音乐闹翻解约，之后她将重心转往内地发展，睽违多年才又再次重新展开演艺事业，但由于张韶涵有许多经典作品都是在福茂时期推出，这也让陈泽杉在脸书爆气开呛：“不懂感恩公司、不懂感恩父母，一个令人失望的艺人”，更狠酸“她现在这么不红，艺人不懂感恩就是走下坡的时候，她也一辈子不会再有那些经典了，新专辑难听死了！”    后期组（总导演代答）有几个导演是B站大神●你们到底是不是全B站大神？粉丝求分享后期组导演的B站账号有几个是    　　随后张韶涵经纪人潘蜜拉表示：张韶涵不认识杉哥，这个也没写名没写姓。    从影以来首度现场收音“这一次是不一样的周润发”此前，《寒战》公映票房口碑双线飘红，并一举斩获香港金像奖最佳影片等九项大奖    我不知道他说的是谁？如果他说的是Angela，那我就不懂一个唱片圈的高层为什么行为却像网路酸民一样？Angela根本和他没有任何私人交情，一个不了解情形的人信口开河的话，我们不予回应。    ”电影中的角色感染了很多人，而影片中金句台词也大受观众热捧，“不是什么人都能得罪的”，“我就是你的黑粉，我黑死你不偿命！”，“他负责作秀，我负责做真人    华纳音乐则表示：杉哥是有感而发，认为艺人是许多歌迷的典范，应该有好的榜样，认为该艺人最红的时候，最经典的歌曲都是出自福茂时期，由福茂唱片一手打造，却不懂感恩，更不懂感恩父母，是非常错误的典范。    传递正能量屏幕内外热衷公益《奔跑吧兄弟》作为一档传递快乐和正能量的节目，在第四季继续推出“全民公益跑”计划', '', '788');
INSERT INTO `article` VALUES ('1033', 'admin', 'UNKNOW', '0', '1469374860', 'UNKNOW', 'UNKNOW', null, 'UNKNOW', '7月24日晚，孙莉通过微博晒和小女儿多妹搞怪合影，并俏皮喊话多妹，称：“妹妹，咱们唠十块钱？”照片中，孙莉将头发盘在后面，画着老年妆容，眼角和额头皱纹十分明显，和孙莉的面貌判若两人，多妹坐在妈妈腿上，调皮的撅着嘴巴学妈妈的样子，十分搞笑。    大张伟说：“这就是我对易烊千玺老师纯纯的爱与尊重，”他认为TFBOYS的青春形象也很符合“甜心儿”的设定，为夏天带来阳光与活力，“带着易烊千玺老师一块上节目，培养我自己的品格，成全别人，陶冶自己    　　此搞笑照片曝光后，网友纷纷围观并留言，称：“妹妹好可爱啊！萌翻天的母女。    李奉圭29日在节目上爆出有3位知名艺人参与了朴有天6月的酒店生日趴，震惊不少观众；而他的一番话也引网友纷纷当起键盘柯南，猜测其中2位艺人可能是主演《太阳的后裔》红遍亚洲的宋仲基，以及演出《请回答1988》爆红的朴宝剑    ”“最可爱的小老奶奶！”“等你老了的时候，也是老美女一个。    然后落地之后就直接被王思聪“召见”了动图看一下妹纸的颜值如何呢~而王思聪在妹纸进来之后说的第一句话是“你脖子好长啊像长颈鹿”咳咳    ”（我是弥尔）', '', '789');
INSERT INTO `article` VALUES ('1034', '人民网', 'UNKNOW', '0', '1469372580', 'UNKNOW', 'UNKNOW', null, 'UNKNOW', '原标题：老旧小区附近居民可申请停车包月      　　老旧小区的停车问题一直是难点，记者从7月22日召开的全市公共停车管理会议上获悉，我市本月出台停车管理新规《关于加强市区公共停车泊位管理的实施意见》，老旧小区附近居民的停车实行包月制，申请人提供房产证、户口簿、行驶证的原件及复印件便可申请。      　　根据公共停车泊位的管理新规，市管道路上的泊位及现有收费停车泊位的收费管理体制不变。市管道路与现有收费停车泊位以外的道路停车泊位由辖区街道办事处负责收费管理，收费管理使用POS机，统一接入市级道路停车管理系统，所收取停车费的90%由街道办事处用于停车设施建设、人员成本支出，10%上缴市级财政。      　　单位或个人利用自有土地、闲置厂房、待建工地开放的临时停车泊位，由产权人自行组织收费。按规定办理相关手续，明码标价、合法使用票据，接受管理部门的监督管理。      　　老旧小区周边的停车泊位收费以优先解决附近居民停车难为原则，计时收费与包月收费相结合，计时停放前25分钟免费，25分钟后根据所在区域按照物价局规定的道路停车收费标准计时收费。      　　老旧小区附近居民的停车实行包月制，由申请人提供房产证、户口簿、行驶证的原件及复印件，对三证统一的车主优先办理包月凭证。      　　包月费由辖区街道办事处根据周边小区内停车收费标准适当调整，原则上略高于小区内收费标准10%左右。停车包月凭证有效期为半年，每半年重新办理。      　　新出台的停车泊位管理制度规定，按区域调整现有收费泊位的免费时段，核心区从现有的10分钟免费时间不变，收费时间早八点至晚八点，夜间免费停放；中心区延长为20分钟免费时间，老旧小区周边收费时间调整为早九点至晚六点，夜间免费停放；主城区延长25分钟免费时间，老旧小区周边收费时间调整为早九点至晚六点，夜间免费停放。（肖慧） (', '', '790');
INSERT INTO `article` VALUES ('1035', '人民网', 'UNKNOW', '0', '1469373120', 'UNKNOW', 'UNKNOW', null, 'UNKNOW', '原标题：无锡入伏以来用电量骤升 调度负荷创历史新高      　　随着锡城出梅、入伏，首波35℃以上的热浪接踵而来。这两天，无锡用电量骤升，迎来了一年一度的用电高峰期。记者从国家电网无锡供电公司获悉，昨天下午13点16分，无锡地区调度负荷突破去年的最高值1028.3万千瓦，达到历史新高。      　　据预计，7月底到8月初将迎来电力负荷最高峰，用电负荷有望超过1100万千瓦。专家表示，今年的用电形势更加严峻，电网设备面临重大考验。      　　用电大数据      　　无锡人一天用电2亿千瓦时      　　从无锡供电公司调控中心了解到，在35℃的高温天气，无锡全社会的用电量也在不断攀升。7月20日，无锡地区调度负荷首次突破1000万千瓦，在13点17分达到1027.9万千瓦。昨天无锡热出了新高度，用电负荷随之噌噌往上。昨天下午13点16分，全市调度负荷突破去年的最高值1028.3万千瓦，创下历史新高。由于35℃高温天还将持续较长的一段时间，预计未来电力负荷还会刷新历史纪录，有望冲击1100万千瓦关口。      　　从电网运行情况来看，目前，无锡人一天的用电量在2亿千瓦时左右。上午7点，用电负荷持续攀升，在上午10点迎来了一天当中的第一个高峰期。中午11点半左右，电力负荷的增长率就有所下降，用电负荷有所下降;中午12点，随着气温的上升，降温设备的持续使用，在13点至14点间达到了一天用电量的第二个高峰，这也是一天电力负荷最高的时候，之后趋于平稳;第三个高峰出现在21点时左右，直到凌晨1点后趋势变缓，并在凌晨4点左右达到最低点。      　　空调提高一度可节电10%      　　一天消耗这么多电量，哪些是用电大户?据供电部门分析，今夏无锡全社会用电最高负荷将增长3%—5%，其中空调负荷已成为影响无锡电网用电负荷的最大因素。“夏季用电量在冲击新的历史峰值时，绝大多数是因为空调使用量的增加，而一般夏季空调用电量占到三成左右。”      　　专家指出，家用空调温度设置每提高一度，大约可节电10%。对耗电量更大的公建单位中央空调来说，控制住空调温度不低于26℃，更具有让电于民和节约开支的双重意义。      　　高温季节停电时间缩短三成      　　据统计，去年7—8月，停电家庭平均停电时间为2.94小时/户，相比2011年同期的3.75小时/户缩短近三成。据运检部门负责人介绍，夏季停电主要发生在老新村，由于设施老化、电力户均容量偏低，如果同时使用大功率的电器很容易引起跳闸。目前，无锡城区还有几万户老新村居民家中的户容量低于2千瓦，也是停电多发区，老新村户均容量的配变增容将持续推进。对于新建小区则不存在这样的担忧，因为新建小区普遍按照不低于8千瓦的户均容量标准建设，出现意外停电的概率也大大降低。      　　为了应对供电形势持续“吃紧”的局面，今年上半年，无锡供电公司完成了石园变、震泽变两个220千伏变电站，以及5个110千伏变电站，供电网络进一步完善，也为市民家中的供电提供了支撑，其中太湖新城的供电可靠性大大提高。      　　夏季每个月抢修电话破万      　　用电高峰也是事故高发期，从配电抢修部了解到，刚刚过去的六月，电网负载较重时，电力供应非常紧张，无锡一个月接到的8000多个抢修电话，7、8、9这三个月期间，每个月抢修电话破万。从故障的停电记录来看，占比最高的要属一些老小区的电力设备，其中开关类的跳闸、烧毁最为常见。目前，城区有33万户开关，但抢修人员不超过500人，严', '', '791');
INSERT INTO `article` VALUES ('1036', '北京晚报', 'UNKNOW', '0', '1469372420', 'UNKNOW', 'beijingwanbao', null, 'UNKNOW', '【男子利用高科技室内种大麻 多所高校学生成客户】2015年，黄某与人合作承租某出租屋，并购买大麻种子、拌料土和LED灯等物品，在室内模拟室外环境种植毒品大麻。之后，黄某将大麻寄送给福州、厦门、泉州等地多所高校的学生，构建毒品贩卖网络。日前涉案6人被提起公诉。http://url.cn/2HCZhCV        查看图片', 'imgurl=http://58.214.246.39:18881/image/imgsearch?shortcode=01-02-2016072500-JnQvIfimgurl=http://58.214.246.39:18881/image/imgsearch?shortcode=01-02-2016072500-quURBf', '792');
INSERT INTO `article` VALUES ('1037', '路透社', 'UNKNOW', '0', '1469289600', 'UNKNOW', 'UNKNOW', null, '路透社', 'DUBAI/WASHINGTONIran confirmed on Sunday the detention of an Iranian-American visiting the country, the latest in a string of arrests of dual nationals in the past year.    Asked about reports of the arrest on national security charges, Judiciary spokesman Gholamhossein Mohseni Ejei told a weekly news conference: \"The report on the arrest of an Iranian-American dual national is correct,\" the semi-official Fars news agency said.    Mohseni Ejei declined to name the individual and said he did not know what specific charges would be lodged. He added that the individual was arrested in the northeastern city of Gorgan, but the trial \"may be held\" in Tehran.    An Iranian-American man, California-based Robin Reza Shahini was detained while visiting his mother in Gorgan earlier in July, according to Shahini\'s friends.    Asked about Shahini\'s case during a news conference last week, U.S. Secretary of State John Kerry said he could not say anything about it \"at this point in time.\" A State Department official said last week that the United States had seen the reports of a possible detention of a U.S. citizen, and were looking into it.    In the past nine months, Iran\'s Revolutionary Guards have arrested at least six dual-national Iranians, their friends and family members say, the highest number of Iranians with dual-nationality detained at one time in recent years to have been acknowledged. The government has confirmed most of the detentions, without giving details of any charges.    The Iranian government does not recognize dual nationality, which prevents relevant Western embassies from seeing individuals who have been detained.    In March, the U.S. State Department issued a warning noting that Iranian-Americans are particularly at risk of being detained or imprisoned if they travel to Iran.    Several Iranian dual nationals from the United States, Britain, Canada and France are being kept behind bars on various charges, including espionage or collaborating with a hostile government. Some are kept to be used for a prisoner exchange with Western countries, according to prisoners, their families and diplomats.    Shahini, in his mid-40s, graduated this spring from San Diego State University, where he studied international security and conflict resolution, said his friend and former classmate, Jasmine Ljungberg. He is set to start a master\'s program in homeland security at the university in the fall, she said.    Ljungberg was last in touch with Shahini via the Whatsapp messaging app on July 9, when Shahini messaged her to share some pictures of a visit to Iran\'s mountainous countryside with his family. Ljungberg said she has been in touch with Shahini\'s girlfriend and briefly with his sister since he was detained.    \"Being a student, it was his dream,\" Ljungberg said. \"He has this passion and this drive to change things.\"    Shahini comes from a poor background, Ljungberg said, and worked a number of jobs after he moved to the United States around 2000 or 2001, including owning a pizza shop and managing a car dealership, before becoming a full-time student.    Shahini was active on social media, including two Facebook accounts, and maintained a blog, but the blog and one of his Facebook accounts appear to have been disabled, Ljungberg said. His Whatsapp account shows someone used the account as recently as Wednesday, July 20, she said.    (Additional reporting by Lesley Wroughton in Washington; Editing by Clelia Oziel)', '', '793');
